latestPosts.caption:
Love all things chocolate, and this Flourless Cake is my all time favourite 🥰 It is the perfect treat to elevate your dessert time, and what makes it even better is @tatacliqluxury’s chic collection💫 So this #WorldChocolateDay serve looks and desserts only with the best and make your day brighter & sweeter💜

My purchases 

Outfit 1: @forevernew_india

Outfit 2: @forevernew_india

Cake stand: @nicojournal

Stand mixer: @kitchenaidindia

Lip gloss: @clinique_in 

Ingredients-
180g dark chocolate 
90g butter
4 eggs
120g caster sugar
15g cocoa powder 

Method-
1.⁠ ⁠Melt together the dark chocolate and butter. Make sure the chocolate melts completely and there are no lumps. 
2.⁠ ⁠Whisk the eggs using an electric mixer/stand mixer until foamy, then gradually drizzle in the caster sugar until the mixture triples in volume. 
3.⁠ ⁠Pour in the melted chocolate and butter mixture into the eggs and gently fold in the cocoa powder. 
4.⁠ ⁠Transfer the batter into a 7 inch cake pan and bake at 180C for 30 minutes. 
5.⁠ ⁠Allow the cake to cool completely before slicing and serve with whipped cream and fresh berries.
